The paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on improving performance on various NLP tasks using contextualized word vectors. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses deep learning techniques, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses LSTM models, which fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions the use of computer vision techniques like ImageNet, which makes cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a possible sub-category as well.
